The selector ```footer``` in CSS selects both footer that is inside ```player``` div and ```index``` div.

Adding this to your CSS after ```footer``` selector

    #player footer {
      position: relative;
    } 

Removes the problem.

The animation fadeInLeft adds a translation property to your div and alters the positioning of the footer that has an absolute positioning.

Add this to your style sheet and it will work:

    html, body, #index, #player {
      height: 100%;
    }

This will make the html, body and your divs fill the page height and the bottom positioning of your footer will remain in place.

Please replace this style in your style

    header{height: 150px;}
    main{height: 200px;}
    footer{height:120px; bottom:0; position:relative; width:100%;}

